<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5322657>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–7. Anthomalachius spinosus (Erichson, 1840), male, apex of left elytra, dorsal (1); appendage in elytral apex, lateral (2); apical tergite (3); apical sternite (4); tegmen (5); aedeagus, lateral (6); locality (7). Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5322657/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5322661>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–16. Anthomalachius strangulatus (Abeille de Perrin,1885), male, right antenna (8); apex of left elytra, dorsal (9); appendage in elytral apex, lateral (10); apical tergite (11); apical sternite (12); tegmen (13); aedeagus, dorsal (14); aedeagus, lateral (15); locality (16). Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5322661/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5322665>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17–25. Anthomalachius senylia (Tshernyshev, 2000), male, right antenna (17); apex of left elytra, dorsal (18); appendage in elytral apex, lateral (19); apical tergite (20); apical sternite (21); tegmen (22); aedeagus, lateral (23); aedeagus, dorsal (24); locality (25). Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5322665/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5322675>
    dc:description "FIGURES 39–44. Anthomalachius spp., male habiti, A. spinosus (Erichson, 1840) (39); A. strangulatus (Abeille de Perrin,1885) (40); A. senylia (Tshernyshev, 2000) (41); A. pseudospinosus (Medvedev, 1964) dorsally (42), and ventrally (43); A. foveatus (Medvedev, 1964) (44). Scale bar 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5322675/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5322669>
    dc:description "FIGURES 26–32. Anthomalachius pseudospinosus (Medvedev, 1964), male, apex of left elytra, dorsal (26); appendage in elytral apex, lateral (27); apical tergite (28); apical sternite (29); tegmen (30); aedeagus, lateral (31); locality (32). Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5322669/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5322673>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33–38. Anthomalachius foveatus (Medvedev, 1964), male, apex of left elytra, dorsal (33); apical tergite (34); apical sternite (35); tegmen (36); aedeagus, lateral (37); locality (38). Scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5322673/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

